          <msContents>
            <summary>
              <p>10 fol. on parchment; Shelfmark: Marcel 10; Qurʾānic Text: Q 10:1-10:15, Q 11:12-12:74; 12 lines per page; Dimensions:  293 x 180mm; Script style: kūfī A.</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>The fragment <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/de/manuscripts/325/page/7r">Arabe 326 (b)</ref> (BNF) belongs to the same manuscript.</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>The catalogue entry by Valery V. Polosin (1939-2014) contains the following information:</p>
              <p>"<hi rend="bold">Marcel 10</hi></p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Two fragments</hi>: <hi rend="bold">10</hi>:1(1)–16(15); <hi rend="bold">11</hi>:15(12) – <hi rend="bold">12</hi>:74(74).</p>
              <p>10 fol. 172/180×293 mm (1.62/1.7). <hi rend="bold">Support</hi>: parchment, thin and transparent. <hi rend="bold">Writing</hi> <hi rend="bold">material</hi>: brown ink.</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Collation</hi>: fragments of three quires.</p>
              <p>I: F1H; </p>
              <p>II: H2F F3H H4F F5H / H6F F7H H8F F9H</p>
              <p>III: F10H</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Text layout:</hi> 12 lines, 142×237 mm (1.666). <hi rend="bold">Ruling</hi>: with a hard-point tool; on some folios there punctures on the margins. <hi rend="bold">Script</hi>: A?, small hand. <hi rend="bold">Diacritis</hi>: rare, the signs are in the same ink as the main text. For letter ف (<hi rend="italic">fā</hi>) a sublinear stroke is used, and for ق (<hi rend="italic">qāf</hi>) – a single dot above the letter. <hi rend="bold">Vocalization</hi>: absent.</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Verse markers:</hi> individual verses – diagonal dashes (type 1.1.3); groups of five verses – a red “shoe-shaped” letter ا (<hi rend="italic">alif</hi>); groups of 10 verses – red circles on the line (type 1.A.I); groups of 50 verses – a rectangular box or a square in red paint, with a blank spot in the center, outlined with ink (fol. 3v, 9v); a group of 100 verses – two interwoven ovals in red paint, outlined with ink (fol. 6r).</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Headpieces: </hi>ornamented bands occupying the whole line before the beginning of Surahs 10 and 12, in yellow, green and red paint (fol. 1r and 7r).</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Stitching</hi>: threads are preserved in the punctures.</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Inscriptions</hi>: on the upper margine of f. 1r the Sourah number is written in ink: <hi rend="italic">S. X.</hi></p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Defects</hi>: small stains; a tear on fol. 1; ink has peeled off in some places.</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Old accession numbers</hi>: A. 10 (according to Langlois’ inventory)</p>
              <p>
                <hi rend="bold">Contents:</hi>
              </p>
              <p>Fol. 1r–1v. Surah 10, verse 1(1) – 16(15). Incipit: بسم الله  . Explicit: عصبت ربي [عذاب يوم عظيم] .</p>
              <p>Fol. 2r–7r. Surah 11, verses 15(12) – 123(123)*. Incipit: [عليه كنز أ]و جاء معه ملك.</p>
              <p>Fol. 7r–10v. Surah 12, verses 1(1) – 74(74). Explicit: فما جزاؤه [ان كنتم كاذبين] .</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Other fragments of the same manuscript</hi>: Arabe 326b(?) (BNF)."</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p> </p>
            </summary>
